a leave of absence in 2002 her current research in high diversity forests in ecuador peru and brazil identifies the dominant species of liana communities across the amazon basin and determining the traits that predispose climbing species to proliferating behaviors under forest alteration tags biodiversity biogeography central & south america climate change conservation corridors diversification forests lianas natural resource management neotropical plant evolution south america 2012 leopold leadership program the stanford woods institute for the environment stanford university stanford ca 94305
